==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Guanaco
<hw>Gua*na"co</hw> <pr>(gw⟦adot⟧*n⟦aum⟧"k⟦osl⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Guanacos</plw> <pr>(-k⟦omac⟧z)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[Sp. <ets>guanaco</ets>, Peruv. <ets>huanacu</ets>. Cf.
<er>Huanaco</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A South American mammal
(<spn>Auchenia huanaco</spn>), allied to the llama, but of larger size
and more graceful form, inhabiting the southern Andes and Patagonia. It
is supposed by some to be the llama in a wild state.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>huanaco</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

